# Prefer Dependency Primitives

Before adding new local types, helpers, wrappers, or utilities, check whether an already-installed dependency provides the same thing.

## Prefer Existing Dependency Support

- Use dependency-provided types when they match the runtime cleanly
- Use built-in helpers or utilities from installed libraries before inventing local shims
- Avoid adding project-local wrappers just to recreate a capability that already exists in a dependency

## Add Local Code Only When Needed

- Add a local helper only when dependency support is missing, awkward, or would create worse coupling
- Keep local wrappers thin and intentional when they are actually justified
- If a dependency already ships the correct primitive, prefer using it rather than maintaining a parallel version in the repo
